{
  "texts": [
    "These tasks are usually complex in themselves, so most methods tackle only one of them at a time.",
    "However, in this article, the authors treat every input as a masked motion series.",
    "This means that visible parts are considered input conditions, whereas masked parts are for learning the completion.",
    "Based on the input conditions, the CVAE (Sohn et al. 2015), used in this work, samples and generates new motion sequences.",
    "The authors introduced an action-adaptive modification to give better semantic guidance for the sequence, thus improving the flexibility."
  ]
}